Anyway, what I'm trying to get at is: There is hope.

Hegemons trying to fit everything under their ever widening umbrella can be cut apart into pieces by specialized competitive sites, and these in turn are small enough that competition among them can arise.
The current consolidation of browsing habits into a handful of sites is merely the product of the massive influx that started with the mobile age and flooded the mainstream sites, yet to re-learn the lessons others did before them.
The same mistakes, the same dramas, the same issues and the same outlooks on life and internet culture, though understandably with some variations, will keep repeating themselves because they were the product of human nature.
